Some places are charging $100 now.

Some of the info in this article applies to your 72 bus but it's  
still useful to know how the circuit works:

http://type2.com/library/misc/vwggauge.htm

Replace the sender with the resistors and see if it's the senders  
that's bad. The fuel gauge responds according to these values:

73ohms 1/1 (full)
10ohms R (empty)

